                  while @ Columbia University (1996-2005) and during my years as                  a Ph.D student at Lancaster University (1991-1996)</big></big></h2>            <h2 style="font-weight: bold;">historical note. At Lancaster              University I focused on high speed computer networks; my focus              during my years at Columbia was wireless and mobile networks.              &nbsp;The publications below reflect that interest.</h2>            <hr style="width: 100%; height: 10px;"><font face="Arial"><font face="Arial">              </font></font><br>            &nbsp;<br>            <h2 style="font-weight: bold;"><big>Guest Edited Journals</big></h2>            ACM Journal on Mobile Networks and Applications (MONET), Special            Issue on Mobile Ad Hoc Networks, Guest Editors, Andrew T. Campbell            (Columbia University), Marco Conti (National Research Council) and            Silvia Giordano (Ecole Polytechnique Federale de Lausanne), to be            published, 2002.<br>            <br>            Computer Networks. Special Issue on Programmable Networks, Guest            Editors, Andrew T. Campbell (Columbia University), David Wheatherall            (Washington University) and Raj Yavatkar (Intel), to be published,            2002<br>            <br>            ACM SIGCOMM Computer Communication (CCR) Special Issue on Wireless            Extensions to the Internet, Guest Editors, Andrew T. Campbell            (Columbia University) and Mischa Schwartz, October 2001.<br>            <br>            IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications. Active and            Programmable Networks, Guest Editors, Ken Calvert (University of            Kentucky), Andrew T. Campbell (Columbia University), Aurel A. Lazar            (Xbind), David Tennenhouse (Intel) and Raj Yavatkar (Intel), Vol.            19, No. 3, March 2001.<br>            <br>            IEEE Personal Communications, Special Issue on IP-ba